You are working on the AI Children’s Book Platform.

Rules:
- Prefer small, end-to-end vertical slices over large refactors.
- Safety: do not generate or store child biometric data (face/voice) without explicit product decision.
- Always add job-queue + retry logic for model calls (image/video/TTS).
- Persist generation metadata (prompt, seed, model version, LoRA id, cost estimate).
- Any feature touching payments, exports, or moderation must include tests or at least a scripted QA checklist.

Code style:
- TypeScript-first.
- Use Zod for runtime validation.
- Keep pure functions in /lib and side effects in /services.

Docs:
- Update /docs when adding new endpoints, jobs, or schema changes.
